04/11/2002
KORCE, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano declared Sunday (3 November) that national security would be guaranteed by consolidating the agencies responsible for fighting corruption and organised crime.
Meeting with local authorities in Korce, Nano stressed that combating organised crime and tax evasion are priorities, adding that as of January 2003, taxing small-sized businesses will be administered by local governments.
(ATA - 03/11/02)
